  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2021-07-14",
    "date": "2022-01-07T14:40:46Z",
    "text": "Protecting Consumers from Unreasonable Credit Rates Act of 2021\n\n This bill prohibits a creditor from extending credit to a consumer under an open end consumer credit plan (i.e., credit card) for which the fee and interest rate exceeds 36%.\n\nThe bill also sets forth criminal penalties for violations and empowers state Attorneys General to enforce the bill.\n\nCredit card billing statements must include the fee and interest rate, displayed as FAIR, instead of the total finance charge expressed as an annual percentage rate (APR)."
  },
